{"TopicId":130027,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Pale Red *Dots* ESO | Proxima b confirmed UPDATE 2017 PaleRedDots!!","CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T14:43:41Z","PageNum":8,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:19:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if JWST will be able to directly look at it and check if it has an atmosphere or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind. I apparently missed the post answering my question: it won\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"waterlubber","CreatedById":119333,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:24:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a shame.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHowever, the knowledge of such a planet may change the JWST mission plan in some ways or result in a specially designed telescope. This may be the first planet other than Earth and Mars that humans will land on \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:56:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163887\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022waterlubber\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a shame.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHowever, the knowledge of such a planet may change the JWST mission plan in some ways or result in a specially designed telescope. This may be the first planet other than Earth and Mars that humans will land on \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlans in this directions,\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.nextbigfuture.com/2016/08/upcoming-telescopes-that-will-provide.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.nextbigfuture.com/2016/08/upcoming-telescopes-that-will-provide.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T22:57:24Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 10:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by magnemoe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"78stonewobble","CreatedById":97559,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T00:00:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729346\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472139763\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/45577-shpaget/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002245577\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/45577-shpaget/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Shpaget\u003C/a\u003E: Too strong fixing and there\u0027s no evolution ... which means a simple change in the environment kills them all. Evolution is about variation (and selection).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@ProtoJeb21: A planetary magnetic field is not correlated with rotation or the amount of iron in a core. See the gas giants. From the paper: Proxima B ist probably locked. Also the 0,35 ecc. is a statistical figure, no fixed measurement, it may be less.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInventing life forms on paper is surely fun but science fiction. From the paper: Equilibrium temp. of Proxima B is -39\u00B0 Celsius. It would need a special greenhouse atmosphere (stronger than earth) to keep liquid water. But atmospheric gases are probably gone. Water, if it was present at all, was probably lost during the first few hundred million years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d suggest we (or whoever feels entitled) take a look at Mars and Europa first ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, on the other hand red dwarves last quite a bit longer, potentially giving evolution plenty of time, even if it\u0027s slow... Assuming offcourse habitability of\u00A0planet lasts long enough. Not betting on life on this particular one tho...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever... A small habitable zone, that could last for eg. 50-100 mio. years more (A far cry from over all red dwarf lifespans)... would be a decent beginners backup site. If we can get there... A big if...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-26T00:00:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/26/2016 12:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by 78stonewobble\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CptRichardson","CreatedById":269,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T01:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222730009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472169605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297559\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002278stonewobble\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, 78stonewobble said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, on the other hand red dwarves last quite a bit longer, potentially giving evolution plenty of time, even if it\u0027s slow... Assuming offcourse habitability of\u00A0planet lasts long enough. Not betting on life on this particular one tho...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever... A small habitable zone, that could last for eg. 50-100 mio. years more (A far cry from over all red dwarf lifespans)... would be a decent beginners backup site. If we can get there... A big if...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUh, try \u0027billions\u0027, at least theoretically.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T04:20:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince Nature already paywalled \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v536/n7617/full/nature19106.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethe paper\u003C/a\u003E, have \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso1629/eso1629a.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea preprint\u003C/a\u003E hosted by ESO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnnoyingly, there is a lack of transit detection that manages to mean rather little because they only got to 5% depth. (ie: excludes something neptune sized being edge-on, but for a rocky body in this mass range? \u00AF\\_(\u30C4)_/\u00AF) I\u0027m not touching actual habitability with a 10 km baseline interferometer given the current unknowns.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-28T15:03:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow Proxima b could be habitable, and the challenges it faces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://palereddot.org/opportunities-and-obstacles-for-life-on-proxima-b/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://palereddot.org/opportunities-and-obstacles-for-life-on-proxima-b/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere also seems to be an unconfirmed planet with an orbit of a little less than 200 days, which is mentioned in the article.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-28T15:08:50Z\u0022 title=\u002208/28/2016 03:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aethon","CreatedById":110755,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T18:51:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn interesting article on the effort to find PCen b. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHabitable Planet Reality Check: Proxima Centauri b:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.drewexmachina.com/2016/08/29/habitable-planet-reality-check-proxima-centauri-b/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.drewexmachina.com/2016/08/29/habitable-planet-reality-check-proxima-centauri-b/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T19:30:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, there seems to be a lot of interesting reading in the reference list ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-04T16:09:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere did Proxima b come from?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://palereddot.org/proxima-b-where-did-it-come-from/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://palereddot.org/proxima-b-where-did-it-come-from/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T21:30:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/776493236579885056\u0022 style=\u0022height:289px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is the update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/776532446795927553\u0022 style=\u0022height:333px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T21:49:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitt